<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
This balance thing is a crock.  Three times tonight I mezzed meleers and died to them.  Sure I can mez one right on me provided I don't die before the quickcast goes off or get instastunned.  However, once I got em mezzed, what do I do with em?  One I debuffed and sicked the pet on him.  He ran up to me and killed me while I was trying to dd...hardly equivalent to what I could do to a caster if I were an archer is it?  He did die to the pet after he killed me, and probably lost xp in the process.  I have 44 mind, 30 body 8 matter, all base...so it's not like I put NO points in body either.  <P>Two other times, friendly meleers nearby broke my mez by attacking...they were not in my group so I couldn't tell them not to quickly enough.  Each time, the formerly mezzed player ran to me and wiped me out before the "friendly" players could finish them.  Again...I see NO balance in this situation.  Sure I can mez.  BUT I can't kill em once I do, even with the debuff, even with the pet.  SO I'm left with mezzing and running...oh what a fun game!  And all the realm points I'm raking in!  NOT!<P>I'm not saying that in a flawless group, the mez can't be used to good effect.  But, I need a flawless group to take advantage of my abilities. I have to say a flawless group is simply not available every time I log on. Stealth archers by contrast take out large groups SOLO.  <P>Problem is, sorcs are set up for crowd control in an aggro setting.  The idea is to peel the mob off us before it can kill us, usually by aggro management.  Spells like confusion and amnesia are all very useful for aggro management.  Problem is, there is no aggro, no confuse and no amnesia in RVR.  So all the testing to determine how powerful sorcs should be PvE against yellow and orange cons simply doesn't apply to the rvr setting.  We get mez, we get root, we get pet, period.  Mez only keeps them off us if they aren't damaged.  Root won't even do that if they get too close before you can cast it.  Pets can only keep them off you by killing them, and they don't usually do that quickly enuff to matter. Tanks can't even interpose their bodies to block them from getting to me, so they can't help much... Maybe they could parry??? Hmm finding the perfect group again, sigh  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> <P>Maybe I'll find a perfect group one of these days, and my mezzes will be useful.  More likely I'll get so tired of getting two-shotted by blue con invisible archers that I'll move on to something else instead.  If you wanna spend low levels constantly looking for groups and getting rebuffed, and if you wanna be popular for goblins and tree groups from bout 38-50...by all means take a sorc character.  If you wanna do rvr, take a stealther.  My advice is take a minstrel...they have some crowd control some armor, huge speed, desirability in groups (for speed and for manasong), and they have stealth.  I think this game is likely to become "Stealth age of camelot" very soon as rvrers realize what an enormous unbalancing advantage stealth is.  <P>I spent more time on horses going TO rvr today than I spent IN rvr.  I'm just not getting the enjoyment return for the huge amount of time invested to rvr.  Small group tactics mean I'm the primary archer target.  Large group engagements mean I mez, then die when others not in my group break my mez and get no realm points for the critters I mezzed because the people doing the killing are not in my group. Or the lag is so ridiculous that actually trying to target someone and cast a spell before you are dead becomes pointless...I was having frame rates longer than one second per frame tonight in some spots, with DSL, with 512 meg memory and a 1.1 gig processor.    <P>Given what I DO have invested, I'll keep trying a little longer hoping its mainly my noob status as an rvrer that is to blame.  I don't generally give up that easily, as witnessed by the fact that I'm maybe the second or third sorc on our server to hit 50, but I'm not seeing the point here anymore.  Anyone know what I could get for a level 50 sorc?<P>Taco
</FONT>
