<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Level 50 Sorcerer will probably run you about $500   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P> <BR> Yes the Sorcerer class is purely PvE right now and I am sure will always be unfortunatly.<P> Mythic has not intent of raising the standards of the casters dmg to put out the amount that other classes can which is a shame.<P> The reason they see no need is they figure in our "utility" spells like root, mez, pets, etc...<P> In an RvR situation non of this is even used more then 10% of the time. <P> Plain and simple FACT that our dmg output for our spells needs to be improved. <BR> There should be no reason someone should have to cast on even a caster more then 3 times before they are dead when most any other class can kill us in one shot.<P> But you get people that say "If you wanted to do dmg you should have played a wizard"<P> Well guess what folks Wizards are in the same boat we are and thier spells are do very little dmg also.<P> "Caster dmg ignores armor" HOWEVER with all the resist gear curently our there any class can get thier resists up pretty well. This combined with the fact that casting itself is so messed up is a real let down.<P> 1) QC a spell wait 3 secs afterwards to cast another spell.<P> 2) Get interrupted during a cast you not only wait till cast is done but then wait another 3 secs after.<P> 3) You can add 1 full sec to all your spells from the time u hit your hotkey number till the time the spell even goes off (which is why QC is useless besides being non interruptable)<P> The only thing I do in RvR now is cast Debuff and run, or I go seeking our stealthers to kill with my pet. Both of these are boring and not why I made a sorcerer.<P> We are supposed to be the best CC class in Albion yet we are not. We are the mind specialist class, yet half our mind spells are considered to overpowerful in RvR.<P> I am sorry to say the Sorcerer class is a dieing breed in RvR and its a shame   <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0">
