<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Taco:<P>1) Mez will work on enemy players who have been damaged.<P>2) In some of your scenarios, it sounded like you were too close to the melee when fighting.  After the mez, assuming it sticks on them all and you don't have to recast, relax.  Back up, pick your target, and go.  If it's a yellow con and you've already debuffed, then sic your pet -- time your first DD to hit when your pet does.  You should be able to kill it by the time it gets to you.  Otherwise, run away a bit while your pet is still hacking, or perhaps root (specialized root = 2 second cast time) then back up and nuke. (Of course watch insta-casts if it's a rooted hybrid-class.)<P>If they're clumped up you may need to forget about the debuff for fear of breaking mez.  Still, if you sic pet, DD, then root when the target's away from the group, you'll be able to debuff and continue attacking.<P>Anyway, I relate to your frustration -- been there and felt it.  Yes, we die fast and often.  But there's no other class (in Albion) that has the capacity to so dramatically effect the outcome of a combat, or to handle multiple enemies so well.  Yes -- there is definitely room for improvement.  But until that improvement comes, I think we can do OK some of the time  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Hang in there!<P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
</FONT>
