Yes in some scenarios I WAS too close.  In one case it was a stealth class who I only saw when he tried to backstab me and the bladeturn got it.  I mezzed him with quickcast YAY.  Unfortunately, another meleer was nearby, not in my group, who immediately started hitting him....THAT broke the mez, and the mez victim wisely kept beating on me.  He got realm points for me, and the friendly meleer got realm points for him.  I got rezzed.  <P>In another case, it was a large battle...I ran close (because my mez range sucks) and mezzed fully 15 to 20 mids.  Before I could back off tho, a wizzie cast an AE nuke, broke mez, and the closest mezzed guy ran at me and toasted me.  He could not of course be re-mezzed for a full minute, and even with root, he would have been on top of me by the time it went off (and quickcast was already blown on the mez).  <P>Point is with short ranges, being close is necessary just to cast in the first place.  Again, if I'm in a group of 8, I'm archer bait.  If I travel with a mob, the mez is almost utterly useless because it will be broken so quickly by people in the mob.  In pve the cloth armor was annoying, but there were all sorts of ways to keep mobs from hitting you that involved aggro managment.  Sorcs are good at aggro management, so I only died maybe twice as often as the tanks in pve.  In rvr, there simply IS no aggro to manage.  In the perfect group, I could maybe cast a mez, back off, and watch as the group takes out the enemy one by one.  I have yet to find a perfect group.  With the loss of the ability to remez, something needs to be done to keep the sorc from getting hit.  In PvE that "something" is aggro management.  In RvR, there simply is nothing.  Wizzies have a very good chance of killing players before they get to them with DDs.  Cabalists have AE dots...very nasty.  Theurgs can spam pets and have bubble.  Sorcs, particularly mind sorcs, seem to be dead.  <P>I suffered the same difficulties getting groups as stealth archers did.  I see no comparison however, in the end game.  Stealth archers can solo entire groups.  I have difficulty taking out a tank, even with a pet.  Sure if he attacks me, he'll die to the pet...but he'll kill me and get realm points.  I'll get squat.  <P>Again maybe I'm just an rvr noob...but if there was an even an attempt at balance here, I'm sure not seeing it.  Ya, in rare instances Mez CAN turn the tide of battle, but it's even MORE rare when I'm alive to actually get the realm points for it.  <P>Sorcs are fun from level 38 to 49 because of trees and gobbies...but even that gets repetitive.  My advice stands, until Mythic makes some real changes, don't start a Sorc, play a stealther.<P>BTW the other level 50 sorc on our server that I know of is Corai...and rumor has it she DID sell.
</FONT>
