Well Tequitus,<P>we are lacking in some RvR aspects but I dont think it as bad as you figure. I was up soloing in Hadriens on the weekend. I saw 5 Mids heading straight at me, got a QC mez of and got em all with it (all were yellow/orange to me at 38). Picked a big Orange Troll, cast DoT and send in the pet (a dwarf, heh). He tanks the pet for a bit and I DD while keeping back. I see another waylayer walking past so quickly release the pet and charm another. By this time the Troll is running for me (released pet still hitting him) at about 1/2 hp and far enough away from the main group - debuff, dd dead. I still have a full pet but am down to 20% power and I know mez is coming off soon - send the pet on the other tank and run like hell. I get away, get some RP's and humiliate a group of Mids. I can garante you that any tank the same lvl, in the same situation as me would not have stood a chance.<P>In the full group situation, yes - I'm archer bait. I accept it but also know that as soon as I die, either the archer is about to die or he is running for his life and I'm rezed. The only time I have seen an archer take out a full group of 8 is when the group of 8 was green/grey to the archer (and it still takes an archer with great skill to pull off)- and IMHO this is not a problem.<P>In the large battles I will agree that 90% of the time mez is a waste of time now with the timer. What I usually do now is hang back and let the tanks engage. If I see a tank with multiples on him I will cast the str/con debuff then try and single target mez. The other thing I try to do is watch the archers/casters and try to either DoT em or interupt them.<P>Be adaptive in RvR and make sure your group knows what your doing.<P>Everyone dies in RvR. We actually have one of the more varied roles - how would you like to be a tank - here pound on this door for 15min.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>With the new patch (hopefully this week) we should last longer, all our debuffs should be usefull, our pets run with us and casting speed will depend on dex. I for one, can hardly wait.<P><BR> - Hidien
