Where's i3ullseye in this thread?<P>With all the AE dmg that the wizzies/clerics/cabalists like to throw around for RP, Mezzes are pretty much wasted in large RvR battles. If those casters want a stationary target then let them root/mez themselves.<P>Sorcs really shine in the small skirmishes between 2-4 groups where a team is focused and organized (bottling up the choke points of frontiers that straggling groups rush thru on the way to their armies).<P>Nothing but full organization will dominate any other strategy in RvR. That includes groups with the correct set-up (ie. speed (Minstrel), damage (tanks/wizzies all on /assist), mezzes (sorcs mainly) and healing (clerics). In the field, infilts and scouts can be a part of a group but not in their vicinity.<P>I'm not dictating a full plan outline here and what I posted above is flawed in many details...my point is that Mez and Sorcs have limited use in giant battles...I find debuffs far more useful. Is this enough to keep our RP up? Not compared to AE dmg classes or Scouts..but the same goes for clerics and especially Mid Healers.<P>lol...reading back on this I'm not sure what my point is...but any fix to a problem with Mez in RvR can't be performed by Mythic. Only by the players whose groups and armies utilize it. If you think that your realm mates are breaking your Mezzes and making them useless..don't cast it and announce your choice not to cast it beforehand with your reasons. I know...it seems that we always have to educate people on how to work with Mez...ah well.    <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Tamon Veneficus<BR>48 Sorcerer - Guinevere
