<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR> I still maintain that instakills are way more broken than mez ever was. Mez means you are out of the action for a minute or so. Mezzes are healable and breakable amd so can be gotten around. Instakills take us casters out of the action for WAY longer. If we just lived long enough for the clerics to react I think alot of these problems would be alleviated.  <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I feel your pain. I was involved in the large scale RvR over in Emain last night. Casting mez was pointless so I was into the debuffing and DD mode. I lost count on the number of times I died to single shot archers and backstabbers. I wouldn't mind so much but there is simply no defence especially against the backstab. When 5 players drop one after the other from backstab and the player never even comes unstealthed, there is something wrong. My only hope is that the new buffs we get will alow me to survive that first hit.<P> - Hidien
