<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
If you're standing around in the thick of things like that, set your pet to "aggressive."  It will be able to see through stealth and attack assassins.<P>When moving, I have the pet on defensive so that it doesn't go after neutral MOBs, etc.  But I am constantly spamming the "nearest enemy" key to locate stealthers, and I click "attack" as soon as one pops up.  Again, the pet ignores stealth and goes for the target.<P>Overall, constant motion is always a good thing -- but it's hard to cast while moving (impossible, actually  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> ).<P>As it is now, I die less to assassins than I used to.  Ranged archers are still a problm, though.  If these two "features" are bugs and they someday "fix" them, though, I will be . . . quite displeased.<P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
</FONT>
